## Image Processing Workflow (Fiji / ImageJ)

Raw images generated by the Raspberry Pi timelapse system are processed using Fiji (ImageJ) as follows:

1. Spatial Calibration
2. Import .TIFF image sequence into Fiji
3. Convert images to 8-bit grayscale (if needed)
4. Apply background subtraction to reduce lighting variation
5. Threshold images to isolate organism structure
6. Use particle analysis for movement quantification
7. Separate and measure regions of interest and save Results table
8. (optional) Create a colored mask stack and save as .avi

Export measurements and/or processed images for downstream analysis in Python
